TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(2,20,1);
$b=random(2,20,1);
$c=random(2,20,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Use the Laws of logarithms to rewrite the expression
\[
\log\sqrt{\frac{x^2+$a}{(x^2+$b)(x^3-2)^{$c}}}
\]
in a form with no logarithm of a product, quotient or power.
$BR
After rewriting we have
\[
\log\sqrt{\frac{x^2+$a}{(x^2+$b)(x^3-2)^{$c}}}
= A \log (x^2+$a) + B \log (x^2+$b)+ C \log (x^3-2)
\]
$BR
with the constant
\(A=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
the constant
\(B=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
and the constant
\(C=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = 1/2;
$ans2 = -1/2;
$ans3 = -$c/2;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

